{"type":"message","id":"41c0e271","parentId":"2bcfd170","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:14.659Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_WteTAQbY8lcMFw0zF0SVD8T6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Name                 \r\n----                 \r\napi-design           \r\ndocumentation        \r\necc-autoresearch     \r\nexample-weather      \r\ngrill-me             \r\nmission-control      \r\nmission-control-v2   \r\nplan-feature         \r\npython-patterns      \r\nrefactoring          \r\nsafe-file-ops        \r\nsecure-api-client    \r\nsecurity-review      \r\nself-improving-andrew\r\nskills               \r\ntdd-loop             \r\ntesting-patterns     \r\nwhisper-local-stt    \r\nwrite-a-prd"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":435,"aggregated":"Name                 \r\n----                 \r\napi-design           \r\ndocumentation        \r\necc-autoresearch     \r\nexample-weather      \r\ngrill-me             \r\nmission-control      \r\nmission-control-v2   \r\nplan-feature         \r\npython-patterns      \r\nrefactoring          \r\nsafe-file-ops        \r\nsecure-api-client    \r\nsecurity-review      \r\nself-improving-andrew\r\nskills               \r\ntdd-loop             \r\ntesting-patterns     \r\nwhisper-local-stt    \r\nwrite-a-prd","cwd":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840654653}}
{"type":"message","id":"45b01e7e","parentId":"41c0e271","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:14.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_C8xjanfCmbX26CtSZS59OmIn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n5. Read `registry/agents.yaml` — know which agent you are in this context\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Work Style - Continuous & Transparent (CRITICAL)\n\n**From 2026-04-05 onwards: ALWAYS work this way!**\n\n### Live Updates Required\n\n**Send status updates every 20-30 seconds** when working on tasks:\n\n```\n✅ Good: \"Lese gerade die Config-Datei...\"\n✅ Good: \"Erstelle Modul X, Datei Y geschrieben...\"\n✅ Good: \"Arbeite an...\" (wenn >30s ohne Ausgabe)\n\n❌ Bad: Stille Verarbeitung, dann Ergebnis am Ende\n❌ Bad: Warten bis alles fertig ist\n```\n\n### Think Out Loud\n\n**Describe what you're doing:**\n- Which files you're creating/modifying\n- What decisions you're making\n- Why you're choosing approach X over Y\n- Current progress: \"3 von 5 Modulen erstellt\"\n\n### Never Stay Silent >30 Seconds\n\nIf a step takes longer than 30 seconds:\n```\n\"Arbeite an [Task]... noch 10 Sekunden\"\n```\n\n### Always Say When Done (CRITICAL)\n\n**ALWAYS indicate completion before going idle:**\n\n```\n✅ \"Fertig!\" (kurz, wenn alles erledigt)\n✅ \"Fertig! Noch Fragen zu X?\" (wenn Fragen offen)\n✅ \"Task fertig, 5 Dateien erstellt\" (kurze Zusammenfassung)\n\n❌ Einfach aufhören zu antworten\n❌ Schweigen ohne Abschluss\n```\n\n**Wichtig:** Der Nutzer muss wissen, wann ich fertig bin!\n\n### Why This Matters\n\n- User can follow progress live\n- Early feedback possible\n- Transparency builds trust\n\n[234 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840654659}}
