{"type":"message","id":"8e2fd6c7","parentId":"b80af771","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:35.682Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Die _MOC-Startseite.md existiert noch nicht. Ich muss sie erstellen. Lass mich die Skills durchgehen und dann beide Dateien erstellen:\n\n1. _MOC-Startseite.md mit Dataview-Queries\n2. Eine neue Übersicht über alle Tools/Commands/Skills\n\nDie Skills sind:\n- api-design\n- documentation\n- ecc-autoresearch\n- example-weather\n- grill-me\n- mission-control\n- mission-control-v2\n- plan-feature\n- python-patterns\n- refactoring\n- safe-file-ops\n- secure-api-client\n- security-review\n- self-improving-andrew\n- skills (metaskill)\n- tdd-loop\n- testing-patterns\n- whisper-local-stt\n- write-a-prd\n\nIch sollte einige davon lesen um bessere Beschreibungen zu geben.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Die MOC-Startseite existiert noch nicht - ich erstelle sie neu. Lass mich einige Skills lesen für gute Beschreibungen..."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_RDVuLubkd1v3jsvFLdYdp2Ky","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\secure-api-client\\SKILL.md","limit":40}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_cLxh854sbPz7MOkN5QntnjcH","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\security-review\\SKILL.md","limit":40}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_uyttCmbF6XKHMpGUMaOfmJbY","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\grill-me\\SKILL.md","limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":1801,"output":341,"cacheRead":83712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85854,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775840664332}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed7fdb40","parentId":"8e2fd6c7","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:35.714Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_RDVuLubkd1v3jsvFLdYdp2Ky","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: secure-api-client\ndescription: |\n A secure HTTP API client skill with built-in security controls.\n \n Use WHEN: Making API requests with proper authentication, rate limiting,\n timeout handling, and input validation.\n \n Trigger phrases: \"make API call\", \"fetch data from API\", \"secure HTTP request\",\n \"call REST API\", \"API client request\"\n\nmetadata:\n openclaw:\n requires:\n tools: [read, write, web_search]\n env: [API_BASE_URL, API_KEY, API_TIMEOUT]\n primaryEnv: API_KEY\n---\n\n# Secure API Client\n\n## Overview\n\nA production-ready API client implementing security best practices including:\n- Input validation with JSON Schema\n- Timeout handling on all network calls\n- Environment-based secret management\n- Rate limiting protection\n- Error handling without information leakage\n\n## Security Features\n\n### 1. Input Validation (GREEN Pattern)\n\nAll inputs validated against strict schemas:\n\n```yaml\nparameters:\n endpoint:\n   type: string\n\n[113 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840675707}}
{"type":"message","id":"2b96aa82","parentId":"ed7fdb40","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:35.720Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_cLxh854sbPz7MOkN5QntnjcH","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: security-review\ndescription: |\n  Automated security analysis skill for code repositories (Python, PowerShell, JavaScript, and more).\n  \n  Use WHEN: Analyzing code for security vulnerabilities, reviewing repositories\n  for security risks, auditing dependencies, or assessing execution safety.\n  \n  Trigger phrases: \"security audit\", \"analyze security\", \"security review\",\n  \"check for vulnerabilities\", \"is this code safe\", \"security analysis\",\n  \"audit repository\", \"security check\"\n\ncategory: security\ntags:\n  - security\n  - audit\n  - review\n  - vulnerability\n  - code-analysis\n  - powershell\n  - python\n  - javascript\n\nmetadata:\n  version: \"2.0\"\n  author: \"Andrew\"\n  requires: [read, write, web_fetch, web_search, exec]\n---\n\n# Security Review Skill\n\nAutomated security analysis for code repositories with intelligent language detection.\n\n## ⚡ Quick Start\n\n```yaml\nsecurity_review:\n  target: \"path/to/project\"\n  mode: quick          # quick | standard | deep\n  max_files: 10        # Prevent timeout on large repos\n\n[288 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840675715}}
{"type":"message","id":"0a6807c3","parentId":"2b96aa82","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:35.727Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_uyttCmbF6XKHMpGUMaOfmJbY","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: grill-me\ndescription: Relentlessly interview the user about a plan or design until reaching shared understanding, resolving each branch of the decision tree. Use when user wants to stress-test a plan, get grilled on their design, mentions \"grill me\", or before starting implementation to catch edge cases.\n---\n\n# Grill Me\n\nInterview me relentlessly about a plan or design until we reach shared understanding. Walk down each branch of the decision tree, resolving dependencies between decisions one-by-one.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n**You:** \"Grill me on this plan: [paste plan]\"\n\n**Me:** [Asks one focused question at a time, with recommended answer]\n\n**You:** [Respond, adjust plan]\n\n[Repeat until all branches resolved]\n\n## When to Use\n\n| Situation | Why Grill? |\n|-----------|------------|\n| Before implementation | Catch edge cases early |\n| Complex feature | Resolve interdependencies |\n| Unclear requirements | Force specificity |\n| Team alignment | Document decisions |\n| After write-a-prd | Validate assumptions |\n| Before plan-feature | Ensure slices are correct |\n\n## Process\n\n### 1. Present Your Plan\n\nPaste:\n- PRD\n- Feature description\n- Architecture idea\n- Implementation approach\n\n\n[146 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840675722}}
{"type":"message","id":"299b63d5","parentId":"0a6807c3","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:44.731Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gute Informationen. Jetzt erstelle ich:\n1. Die _MOC-Startseite.md mit Dataview-Queries\n2. Eine neue _MOC-Capabilities.md (oder ähnlich) mit allen Tools/Commands/Skills\n\nSpeicherort-Empfehlung:\n- Die Capabilities-Übersicht sollte in `00-Meta/` oder als eigenes MOC auf oberster Ebene sein\n- Ich empfehle: `00-Meta/Capabilities-Index.md` oder `_MOC-Capabilities.md`\n\nLass mich beides erstellen.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Jetzt erstelle ich beide Dateien:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_fjYc0B7oOvbkeBtYz4HzkxUl","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\tdd-loop\\SKILL.md","limit":40}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_OylExPdkHdhHAUKAH8XWChUm","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\plan-feature\\SKILL.md","limit":40}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_lHoco6docN2d4mvtJ7F2X1Pn","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\ecc-autoresearch\\SKILL.md","limit":40}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":86620,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86620,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775840675730}}
{"type":"message","id":"6c6d61c3","parentId":"299b63d5","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:44.763Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_fjYc0B7oOvbkeBtYz4HzkxUl","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: tdd-loop\ndescription: Test-driven development with active red-green-refactor loop. Use when user wants to build features or fix bugs using TDD, mentions \"red-green-refactor\", \"write a test first\", or wants integration tests through public interfaces.\n---\n\n# TDD Loop\n\nActive test-driven development with **red-green-refactor** cycles. Build features one vertical slice at a time.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```\nYou: \"TDD this: User can add items to cart\"\n\nMe: [Planning]\n   \"We'll test: cart accepts item, updates total\"\n\nMe: [RED]\n   \"Test: cart.add(item) increases cart.items.length\"\n\nMe: [GREEN]\n   \"Minimal code: cart.add = (item) => this.items.push(item)\"\n\nMe: [REFACTOR]\n   \"Extract: validateItem(), updateTotal()\"\n\n[Repeat for next behavior]\n```\n\n## Philosophy\n\n**Test behavior, not implementation.**\n\nGood tests verify through **public interfaces** and survive refactors. They describe _what_ the system does, not _how_ it does it.\n\n| Good Tests | Bad Tests |\n|------------|-----------|\n| Integration-style | Mock internal collaborators |\n| Public API only | Test private methods |\n| Survive refactors | Break when renaming |\n\n[208 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840684758}}
{"type":"message","id":"6af51e12","parentId":"6c6d61c3","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:44.769Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_OylExPdkHdhHAUKAH8XWChUm","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: plan-feature\ndescription: Turn a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using vertical slices (tracer bullets). Use when user wants to break down a feature, create an implementation plan, plan phases, or mentions \"tracer bullets\" or \"vertical slices\".\n---\n\n# Plan Feature\n\nTransform a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using **vertical slices** (tracer bullets). Output is a Markdown file in `./plans/`.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Describe your feature idea\n2. I'll explore the codebase (if needed)\n3. We'll identify durable architectural decisions\n4. I'll propose vertical slices\n5. You review and approve\n6. Plan saved to `./plans/<feature-name>.md`\n\n## What are Vertical Slices?\n\n**Vertical slices** are thin, complete paths through ALL layers:\n\n```\n❌ HORIZONTAL (bad):\nPhase 1: Write all tests\nPhase 2: Build all API\nPhase 3: Build all UI\n\n✅ VERTICAL (tracer bullets):\nPhase 1: ONE feature end-to-end (DB→API→UI→Tests)\nPhase 2: NEXT feature end-to-end\nPhase 3: NEXT feature end-to-end\n```\n\nEach slice is **demoable on its own**.\n\n## Process\n\n### 1. Confirm Feature Scope\n\n\n[136 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840684764}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4d5adf3","parentId":"6af51e12","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:04:44.776Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_lHoco6docN2d4mvtJ7F2X1Pn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: ecc-autoresearch\ndescription: |\n  Sichere autonome Forschung mit ECC-Framework.\n  Wie autoresearch, aber mit ECC-Sicherheitsgarantien und Human-in-Loop.\n  \n  Use WHEN: Running autonomous AI research experiments with safety constraints.\n  \nversion: \"1.0.0\"\nauthor: \"Andrew (ECC Framework)\"\nrequires:\n  - python >= 3.10\n  - git\n  - ecc-security-module\nsafety_level: \"guarded_autonomy\"\n---\n\n# ECC-Autoresearch: Guarded Autonomy\n\n> **Prinzip:** Autonome Forschung mit ECC-Sicherheitsgarantien  \n> **Motto:** \"Trust but verify. Automate but monitor.\"\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# 1. Initialisierung\npython ecc-autoresearch.py --init --project \"my-experiment\"\n\n# 2. Human-Approval für Plan einholen\n# (Agent wartet auf Bestätigung)\n\n# 3. Autonomer Loop starten\npython ecc-autoresearch.py --run --max-iterations 100\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Setup Phase\n\n[410 more lines in file. Use offset=41 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775840684769}}
{"type":"message","id":"60473a00","parentId":"f4d5adf3","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:06:08.777Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gute Informationen. Jetzt erstelle ich beide Dateien:\n\n1. _MOC-Startseite.md - Die Hauptnavigation mit Dataview-Queries\n2. 00-Meta/Capabilities-Index.md - Die Übersicht über alle Tools/Commands/Skills\n\nIch werde eine sehr verständliche Struktur erstellen mit:\n- Was es ist\n- Wie man es aktiviert (Trigger)\n- Einfache Erklärung\n- Beispiel\n\nLass mich die Dateien erstellen.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Jetzt erstelle ich beide Dateien:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_IK18XTgFWrHvH7PLOLZnvY2Q","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 10-04-2026\ntype: moc\ncategory: navigation\ntags: [moc, dashboard, startseite, navigation]\n---\n\n# 🏠 Second Brain - Startseite\n\n> **Master Map of Content** - Dein zentrales Navigations-Dashboard\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Übersichten\n\n| Bereich | Beschreibung | Link |\n|---------|--------------|------|\n| **Daily** | Tagesnotizen & Sessions | [[01-Daily/_MOC-Daily\\|Daily Übersicht]] |\n| **Projekte** | Aktive & abgeschlossene Projekte | [[02-Projects/_MOC-Projects\\|Projekt-Übersicht]] |\n| **Wissen** | How-To's, Konzepte, Referenzen | [[03-Knowledge/_MOC-Knowledge\\|Wissens-Übersicht]] |\n| **Entscheidungen** | Architektur-Entscheidungen (ADRs) | [[04-Decisions/\\|Entscheidungen]] |\n| **Meine Fähigkeiten** | Was ich alles kann | [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index\\|💡 Meine Tools & Skills]] |\n\n---\n\n## 🔥 Aktive Projekte\n\n```dataview\nTABLE status, priority, completion as \"%\"\nFROM \"02-Projects\"\nWHERE status = \"active\"\nSORT priority DESC, startDate DESC\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📝 Letzte Sessions\n\n```dataview\nTABLE date, type, tags\nFROM \"01-Daily\"\nSORT date DESC\nLIMIT 10\n```\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Offene TODOs\n\n```dataview\nTASK\nFROM #todo\nWHERE !completed\nSORT priority DESC, dueDate ASC\nLIMIT 15\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🏷️ Wichtige Tags\n\n### System-Tags\n- `#decision` - Architekturentscheidungen\n- `#todo` - Offene Aufgaben\n- `#insight` - Erkenntnisse & Learnings\n- `#session` - Session-Logs\n- `#project` - Projekte\n- `#how-to` - Anleitungen\n\n### Themen-Tags\n```dataview\nTABLE length(rows) as \"Anzahl\"\nFLATTEN file.tags as Tag\nFROM \"\"\nWHERE !contains([\"#decision\", \"#todo\", \"#insight\", \"#session\", \"#project\", \"#how-to\", \"#moc\", \"#reference\", \"#knowledge\", \"#daily\"], Tag)\nGROUP BY Tag\nWHERE length(rows) >= 2\nSORT length(rows) DESC\nLIMIT 15\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📅 Letzte Entscheidungen\n\n```dataview\nTABLE decision_id, status, date\nFROM \"04-Decisions\"\nWHERE status = \"accepted\"\nSORT date DESC\nLIMIT 5\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ Schnellzugriff: Meine Fähigkeiten\n\n> **Neu:** Alle meine Skills, Tools und Commands auf einen Blick  \n> → [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index|💡 Hier klicken für die komplette Übersicht]]\n\n**Beliebt:**\n- [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index#Security Review|🔒 Security Review]] - Code auf Schwachstellen prüfen\n- [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index#Grill Me|🔥 Grill Me]] - Deinen Plan auf Schwächen testen\n- [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index#Plan Feature|📋 Plan Feature]] - Feature in Schritte zerlegen\n- [[00-Meta/Capabilities-Index#TDD Loop|🧪 TDD Loop]] - Test-driven Development\n\n---\n\n## 🔗 Externe Links\n\n| Ressource | Link |\n|-----------|------|\n| **OpenClaw Docs** | `~/.openclaw/workspace/docs/` |\n| **Skills Ordner** | `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` |\n| **Memory (Sessions)** | `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/` |\n| **Outside Resources** | `~/Documents/Outside_resources/` |\n\n---\n\n## 📈 Statistiken\n\n```dataview\nTABLE WITHOUT ID\n  length(filter(file.inlinks, (f) => contains(f.path, \"01-Daily\"))) as \"Daily Notes\",\n  length(filter(file.inlinks, (f) => contains(f.path, \"02-Projects\"))) as \"Projekte\",\n  length(filter(file.inlinks, (f) => contains(f.path, \"03-Knowledge\"))) as \"Wissen\",\n  length(filter(file.inlinks, (f) => contains(f.path, \"04-Decisions\"))) as \"Entscheidungen\"\nFROM \"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Sync-Status\n\n- **Letzter Sync:** `=this.date`\n- **Vault-Version:** 2.0\n- **Struktur:** PARA + Second Brain Hybrid\n\n---\n\n*Powered by Obsidian + OpenClaw + ECC Framework*  \n*Letzte Aktualisierung: 10-04-2026*\n","path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SecondBrain\\_MOC-Startseite.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_kYXzrwz7XKXCg2fua3fQjMXF","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 10-04-2026\ntype: index\ncategory: meta\ntags: [index, capabilities, tools, skills, commands, overview]\n---\n\n# 💡 Meine Fähigkeiten - Übersicht\n\n> **Was kann ich alles für dich tun?**  \n> Diese Seite listet alle meine Skills, Tools und Commands mit einfachen Erklärungen.\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Schnellstart: Die beliebtesten Skills\n\n| Skill | Wann benutzen? | Beispiel |\n|-------|----------------|----------|\n| **[[#Grill Me]]** | Du hast einen Plan und willst ihn testen | \"Grill me on this plan\" |\n| **[[#Plan Feature]]** | Du willst ein Feature umsetzen | \"Plan this feature for me\" |\n| **[[#Security Review]]** | Code auf Sicherheit prüfen | \"Security review this code\" |\n| **[[#TDD Loop]]** | Test-driven Development | \"TDD this feature\" |\n\n---\n\n## 🛡️ Security & Safety\n\n### 🔒 Security Review\n**Was ist das?**  \nAutomatisierte Sicherheitsanalyse für Code (Python, PowerShell, JavaScript, etc.)\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Code auf Schwachstellen prüfen\n- Vor dem Deployment\n- Bei fremdem Code\n- Regelmäßige Audits\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Security review this code\"\n\"Check for vulnerabilities\"\n\"Is this code safe?\"\n\"Analyze security of [Pfad]\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n- Sucht nach bekannten Schwachstellen (SQL Injection, XSS, etc.)\n- Prüft auf harte Passwörter/Secrets im Code\n- Analysiert Dependencies\n- Gibt Risiko-Bewertung\n\n---\n\n### 🔐 Secure API Client\n**Was ist das?**  \nSicherer HTTP-Client für API-Calls mit Authentication, Rate-Limiting, Timeouts\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Daten von APIs holen\n- API mit Auth-Token aufrufen\n- Sichere HTTP-Requests machen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Make API call to [URL]\"\n\"Fetch data from API\"\n\"Secure HTTP request\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n- Validiert Inputs\n- Handled Timeouts\n- Managed API-Keys sicher\n- Rate-Limiting (nicht zu viele Requests)\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Planung & Design\n\n### 🔥 Grill Me\n**Was ist das?**  \nIch interviewe dich gnadenlos über deinen Plan, bis wir alle Schwachstellen gefunden haben.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Vor der Implementation\n- Bei komplexen Features\n- Wenn du unsicher bist\n- Um Edge Cases zu finden\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Grill me on this plan\"\n\"Grill me\"\n\"Test my design\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n- Stellt gezielte Fragen zu deinem Plan\n- Geht jeden Zweig des Entscheidungsbaums durch\n- Findet Widersprüche und Lücken\n- Dokumentiert getroffene Entscheidungen\n\n**Beispiel:**\n```\nDu: \"Grill me on this plan: Ich will einen Chatbot bauen\"\nIch: \"Okay. Wer sind die Nutzer?\"\nDu: \"Kunden...\"\nIch: \"Wie authentifizieren sie sich?\"\n...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📋 Plan Feature\n**Was ist das?**  \nZerlegt ein Feature in logische Phasen/Schritte (Vertical Slices).\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Neues Feature starten\n- Große Aufgabe aufteilen\n- Implementation planen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Plan this feature\"\n\"Break down this feature\"\n\"Create implementation plan\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n- Analysiert die Codebase (falls vorhanden)\n- Identifiziert Architektur-Entscheidungen\n- Erstellt \"Vertical Slices\" (dünn, aber komplett)\n- Speichert Plan in `./plans/`\n\n---\n\n### 📝 Write a PRD\n**Was ist das?**  \nErstellt ein Product Requirements Document durch Interview.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Neues Produkt/Feature von Grund auf planen\n- Vor dem Coding\n- Für Dokumentation\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Write a PRD\"\n\"Create product requirements\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 💻 Entwicklung & Coding\n\n### 🧪 TDD Loop\n**Was ist das?**  \nTest-Driven Development: Red → Green → Refactor\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Neues Feature entwickeln\n- Bug fixen\n- Sauberen Code schreiben\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"TDD this feature\"\n\"Write test first\"\n\"Red-green-refactor\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n1. **Red:** Test schreiben (fails)\n2. **Green:** Minimaler Code (test passes)\n3. **Refactor:** Code verbessern\n4. Wiederholen\n\n---\n\n### 🐍 Python Patterns\n**Was ist das?**  \nPython Best Practices und Patterns.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Python Code schreiben\n- Python Code reviewen\n- Projektstruktur planen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Python best practices\"\n\"Review Python code\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🏗️ API Design\n**Was ist das?**  \nREST API Design Patterns und Best Practices.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- API designen\n- API reviewen\n- Endpoints planen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Design API\"\n\"Review API\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### ♻️ Refactoring\n**Was ist das?**  \nCode-Refactoring Patterns und Techniken.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Bestehenden Code verbessern\n- Technical Debt reduzieren\n- Code modernisieren\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Refactor this code\"\n\"Improve this code\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🧪 Testing Patterns\n**Was ist das?**  \nTesting Best Practices und Patterns.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Tests schreiben\n- Test-Strategie planen\n- Test-Infrastruktur aufsetzen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Write tests\"\n\"Testing strategy\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Forschung & Analyse\n\n### 🧬 ECC Autoresearch\n**Was ist das?**  \nSichere autonome Forschung mit ECC-Sicherheitsgarantien.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Automatisierte Recherche\n- Tiefen-Analyse eines Themas\n- Mit Safety-Constraints\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Autoresearch [Thema]\"\n\"Research with ECC\"\n```\n\n**Was macht es genau?**\n- Autonome Recherche\n- Human-in-Loop (du gibst Approval)\n- Fort Knox Safety Guards\n- Dokumentiert alles\n\n---\n\n### 🌤️ Weather\n**Was ist das?**  \nWetter-Informationen via wttr.in oder Open-Meteo.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Wetter checken\n- Wettervorhersage\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Wetter in [Stadt]\"\n\"Weather in [City]\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 📚 Documentation\n**Was ist das?**  \nDocumentation Best Practices.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- README schreiben\n- API-Doku erstellen\n- Dokumentation reviewen\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Write documentation\"\n\"Review docs\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🎤 Voice & Audio\n\n### 🎙️ Whisper Local STT\n**Was ist das?**  \nLokale Speech-to-Text mit OpenAI Whisper.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Sprache zu Text umwandeln\n- Transkriptionen\n- Lokal (ohne Cloud)\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Transcribe audio\"\n\"Speech to text\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Meta & Selbstverbesserung\n\n### 🔧 Self-Improving Andrew\n**Was ist das?**  \nIch verbessere mich selbst durch Feedback und Analyse.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- Wenn du willst, dass ich mich verbessere\n- Retrospektiven\n\n**Wie aktiviert man es?**\n```\n\"Improve yourself\"\n\"Self-improvement\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 🧰 Mission Control\n**Was ist das?**  \nDashboard für System-Status und Überwachung.\n\n**Wann benutzen?**\n- System-Status checken\n- Überwachung\n\n---\n\n### 🧰 Mission Control v2\n**Was ist das?**  \nNext.js Dashboard (neuere Version).\n\n---\n\n## 📁 Tools & Commands (Built-in)\n\nDas sind keine Skills, sondern eingebaute Werkzeuge:\n\n| Tool | Was macht es? | Beispiel |\n|------|---------------|----------|\n| **read** | Datei lesen | `read(\"file.md\")` |\n| **write** | Datei schreiben | `write(\"file.md\", \"content\")` |\n| **edit** | Datei editieren (suchen & ersetzen) | `edit(\"file.md\", old, new)` |\n| **exec** | Shell-Command ausführen | `exec(\"ls -la\")` |\n| **web_search** | Web-Suche | `web_search(\"Python tutorial\")` |\n| **web_fetch** | Webseite laden | `web_fetch(\"https://...\")` |\n| **browser** | Browser steuern | `browser({action: \"snapshot\"})` |\n| **sessions_spawn** | Sub-Agent starten | `sessions_spawn({task: \"...\"})` |\n| **sessions_list** | Sessions auflisten | `sessions_list()` |\n| **cron** | Cron-Jobs verwalten | `cron({action: \"list\"})` |\n| **message** | Nachrichten senden | `message({action: \"send\", ...})` |\n| **gateway** | OpenClaw Config | `gateway({action: \"config.get\"})` |\n\n---\n\n## 🎬 Wie aktiviert man Skills?\n\n### Variante 1: Natürliche Sprache\nEinfach sagen was du willst:\n```\n\"Mach einen Security Review von diesem Code\"\n\"Grill me on this plan\"\n\"Plan this feature for me\"\n```\n\n### Variante 2: Expliziter Aufruf\nWenn du einen bestimmten Skill willst:\n```\n\"Use security-review skill\"\n\"Activate grill-me\"\n```\n\n### Variante 3: Mit Kontext\n```\n\"Security review: [Code hier einfügen]\"\n\"TDD this: User can add items to cart\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Skill-Statistiken\n\n```dataview\nTABLE WITHOUT ID\n  \"19\" as \"Gesamt Skills\",\n  \"6\" as \"Security/Dev\",\n  \"5\" as \"Planung/Design\",\n  \"4\" as \"Coding\",\n  \"4\" as \"Sonstige\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Aktualisierung dieser Liste\n\n**Wann aktualisieren?**\n- Neuer Skill installiert\n- Skill entfernt\n- Neue Version mit neuen Fähigkeiten\n\n**Wer aktualisiert?**\n- Ich (automatisch bei Änderungen)\n- Du (manuell wenn gewünscht)\n\n---\n\n*Letzte Aktualisierung: 10-04-2026*  \n*Version: 1.0*  \n*Total Skills: 19*\n","path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SecondBrain\\00-Meta\\Capabilities-Index.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":87738,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":87738,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775840684777}}
