{"type":"message","id":"e44fedc0","parentId":"89f3a570","timestamp":"2026-04-10T19:52:20.571Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_i6owJUZ9uE0yQfHYYaS0iFUj","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verzeichnis: C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\r\n\r\n\r\nMode                 LastWriteTime         Length Name                                                                 \r\n----                 -------------         ------ ----                                                                 \r\nd-----        10.04.2026     17:16                memory                                                               \r\nMemory directory ready"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":461,"aggregated":"Verzeichnis: C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\r\n\r\n\r\nMode                 LastWriteTime         Length Name                                                                 \r\n----                 -------------         ------ ----                                                                 \r\nd-----        10.04.2026     17:16                memory                                                               \r\nMemory directory ready","cwd":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775850740570}}
{"type":"message","id":"b0c0c0f1","parentId":"e44fedc0","timestamp":"2026-04-10T19:53:00.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll append the memories to memory/2026-04-10.md","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_IwaLZW3G3EsVrEDfgb6UGBMv","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Session Log: 10-04-2026\n\n## Major Accomplishments\n\n### 1. SecondBrain Extension - COMPLETED (3 Phases)\n- **Phase 1:** Inbox system (00-Meta/Inbox/, template, README)\n- **Phase 2:** Session-Logs (enhanced Daily.md with session_id, tokens_used, agent_mode, projects)\n- **Phase 3:** DataviewJS Dashboard (_MOC-Startseite.md with token statistics, session metrics)\n- All 14 tests passed\n- Duration: ~2 hours\n\n### 2. Complete Analysis of ECC-Framework\n- Analyzed ALL 31 files in ECC-SecondBrain-Framework\n- Status: 100% complete\n- Discovered previously missed Critical-Bug documentation (edit-tool bug)\n- Migrated useful components: Areas, Dataview queries\n- Created systematic analysis workflow to prevent future omissions\n\n### 3. Areas System Implemented\n- Created 02-Areas/ directory\n- area-development.md (weekly review, technical)\n- area-research.md (monthly review, knowledge)\n- README.md explaining PARA Areas concept\n\n### 4. Auto-Sync Cron Job\n- Created cron job: \"Auto-Sync SecondBrain alle 8h\"\n- Interval: Every 8 hours (28,800,000 ms)\n- Syncs OpenClaw to Obsidian automatically\n\n### 5. Enhanced Decision Template\n- Created Decision-v2.md based on ECC-Framework template\n- Features: Status tracking, Consequences (pos/neg/neutral), Alternatives table, Related decisions\n- Backup created before modification\n\n### 6. Symlink Setup Completed\n- Successfully created skills/ symlink to ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills\n- Enables WikiLinks to work in Obsidian\n- Created setup-symlinks.ps1 and check-vault-health.ps1 scripts\n- All PowerShell encoding issues resolved (ASCII-only, no emojis)\n\n### 7. Documentation Created\n- workflow-vollstaendige-analyse-garantieren.md (systematic analysis process)\n- workflow-aktives-memory-lesen.md (preventing MEMORY.md oversights)\n- erweiterte-dataview-queries.md (extended dashboard queries)\n- powershell-scripting-lessons-learned.md (encoding, syntax best practices)\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n1. **Analysis Method:** Established 5-phase process (Inventory → Categorization → File-by-file → Verification → Confirmation)\n2. **ECC-Framework Integration:** Migrated Areas and Dataview queries, skipped plugin (using cron instead)\n3. **Template Strategy:** Keep both Decision.md and Decision-v2.md for comparison/testing\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\n- **Critical:** Always use explicit Boolean comparisons in PowerShell (-eq $true, not just $_.Success)\n- **Critical:** Never use write() for existing files - only edit() or read()+write() with verification\n- **Critical:** Count files BEFORE analysis, verify AFTER (100% = analyzed/total)\n- **Important:** Areas (PARA method) complement Projects - continuous responsibility vs. finite goals\n\n## Statistics\n\n- Files created: 15+\n- Tests passed: 14/14\n- Backups created: 4\n- Total session time: ~4 hours\n- Vault version: 2.1 (with DataviewJS and Areas)\n\n## Next Steps (Future Sessions)\n\n1. Analyze remaining archive folders:\n   - Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/\n   - Master Rework 06.04.2026/ (3 missing documents)\n   - Other loose files (AI_AGENT_WORK_INSTRUCTION.md, etc.)\n\n2. Test new features in Obsidian:\n   - Dataview plugin functionality\n   - Areas review workflow\n   - Inbox processing\n\n## Work Ethic Applied\n\n\"Finish what we start. Come what may.\" - Completed SecondBrain extension as planned, systematic approach with tests after each phase, documented all learnings for future sessions.\n\n---\nSession closed: 21:51 CET\n","path":"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-04-10.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":186999,"output